# 7. 今はただ、この一射を

Mafuyu: Okay, we'll go with the rules we just discussed. We'll each have four arrows and alternate each time we shoot.
Mafuyu: In the event of a tie... We're supposed to keep going, but we can call it a draw to avoid staying too late.
Shizuku: Yes, I agree. Let's both do our best.
Shizuku: (Ultimately, I wasn't able to learn what was bothering Asahina... I'm still in the dark...)
Shizuku: (Which likely means that I won't be able to help her...)
Shizuku: (But that's okay for now...)
Shizuku: (Someday, as long as I'm able to lend her a hand when she does need me...)
Shizuku: (So, for now... I need to become stronger.)
Shizuku: (I have to learn how to become a pillar of support for someone when they need me most.)
Shizuku: (And archery may actually help me achieve that goal...)
Mafuyu: Okay, Hinomori, shall we begin?
Shizuku: Yes.
Mafuyu: I'll be going first.
Shizuku: (As usual, she had no trouble hitting her mark...)
Shizuku: (It never ceases to amaze me. She's able to stay so focused but still relaxed as she fires each arrow...)
Shizuku: (While I'm the complete opposite.)
Shizuku: (I always have so much trouble drawing since my right elbow and wrist have a habit of tightening up when I do.)
Shizuku: (And the more I try, the worse it gets. Just like when things weren't going well for me...)
Shizuku: (But now...)
Shizuku: (Things feel different. I think I can nearly match her...)
Mafuyu: (Hinomori's staying so calm...)
Mafuyu: (This contest may actually end with a draw.)
Mafuyu: ...!
Shizuku: Huh? That sound...
Mafuyu: I'm so sorry. I made sure to place it in my bag, but I forgot to put it on silent...
Mafuyu: I know we're still having our contest, but I'll need to step out for a second.
Shizuku: Um... Yes, of course.
Mafuyu: (It's Mom...)
Mafuyu's Mother's Message: <Okay. Come home soon.>
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (It's nothing out of the ordinary...)
Mafuyu: (But why do I feel so...?)
Shizuku: Asahina...?
Mafuyu: Oh...
Shizuku: Did something come up? Should we...?
Mafuyu: Uh, no... It's okay. Just three more shots and we'll be finished.
Mafuyu: I'll go now...
Shizuku: O-Okay...
Shizuku: (What happened just now...? She suddenly seems so...)
Mafuyu: ...!
Shizuku: *Gasp*
Shizuku: (She missed...!)
Shizuku: (What's going on...? She's usually able to keep herself steady even when her focus lapses for a split second...)
Mafuyu: It's your turn, Hinomori...
Shizuku: Oh, right...
Shizuku: (Calm your mind... Otherwise, you won't be able to hit the target...)
Shizuku: (Breathe... Focus only on pulling the bowstring back...)
Shizuku: (Thank goodness... I hit it, but just barely...)
Shizuku: (It's so strange how archery has this way of revealing your true mental state...)
Shizuku: (And it's Asahina's turn now...)
Mafuyu: ...
Shizuku: (Asahina...)
Shizuku: (She's tensing up...)
Shizuku: (Her shoulders and elbows... They seem completely frozen.)
Mafuyu: ...
Shizuku: (What changed just now...? Is it because of that message...?)
Shizuku: (Maybe we should stop for now... But...)
Shizuku: (No, I made my decision earlier... I'm going to help her when she truly needs it.)
Shizuku: (And I can do that now...)
Shizuku: Just breathe, Asahina...
Mafuyu: Huh...?
Shizuku: I don't know what's going through your head right now.
Shizuku: But I'm sure you'll be able to calm yourself like you usually do...
Shizuku: So, for now, just focus on this one shot.
Mafuyu: Hinomori...
Shizuku: I know you can.
Shizuku: (You can do it, Asahina...!)
Shizuku: *Gasp* It hit...!
Mafuyu: *Sigh*
Shizuku: You're amazing, Asahina...! That was such an incredible shot...!
Mafuyu: Thank you, Hinomori...
Mafuyu: But this contest still isn't over. Please give it your best shot.
Shizuku: Yes, I plan to...!
